%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-billionaire-selena-gomez-makes-spends-her-fortune-2024-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Selena%20Gomez%20is%20officially%20a%20billionaire%20more%20than%20two%20decades%20after%20audiences%20first%20met%20her%20on%20%26quot%3BBarney%20%26amp%3B%20Friends.%26quot%3B%20Her%20net%20worth%20is%20now%20%241.3%20billion.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ledmonds%40businessinsider.com%20(Lauren%20Edmonds%2CJennifer%20Hussein%2CMadeline%20Berg)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A304%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-billionaire-selena-gomez-makes-spends-her-fortune-2024-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Russia%20is%20exploiting%20this%20outdated%20election%20law%20to%20pay%20American%20influencers%20to%20sway%20voters%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221885%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20US%20Capitol%20is%20edited%20with%20red%20and%20blue.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66de08d183b8099cf9fca407%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20DOJ%20accused%20Russia%20of%20a%20foreign%20influence%20plot%20again.%3Cp%3EDouglas%20Rissing%2FGetty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Justice%20Department%20says%20Russia%20used%20American%20influencers%20to%20spread%20Russian%20propaganda.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20FEC%20has%20outdated%20rules%20around%20influencers%20promoting%20political%20content%20for%20profit.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt%20is%20a%20potentially%20valuable%20loophole%20for%20foreign%20powers.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%20has%20long%20used%20social%20media%20to%20launch%20disinformation%20campaigns%20to%20sway%20the%20American%20public%20during%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20some%20social%20media%20companies%20have%20worked%20to%20prevent%20the%20spread%20of%20questionable%20content%2C%20Russia%20seems%20to%20have%20found%20a%20new%2C%20perfectly%20legal%20way%20in%3A%20influencers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Justice%20Department%20on%20Wednesday%20filed%20conspiracy%20charges%20against%20two%20Russian%20nationals%20who%20Attorney%20General%20Merrick%20Garland%20said%20engaged%20in%20a%20%26quot%3B%2410%20million%20scheme%20to%20create%20and%20distribute%20content%20to%20US%20audiences%20with%20hidden%20Russian%20government%20messaging.%26quot%3B%20He%20called%20it%20a%20Russian%20attempt%20to%20%26quot%3Bexploit%20our%20country's%20free%20exchange%20of%20ideas%20in%20order%20to%20covertly%20further%20its%20own%20propaganda%20efforts.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDaniel%20Weiner%2C%20the%20Elections%20and%20Government%20Program%20director%20at%20the%20Brennan%20Center%20for%20Justice%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20the%20case%20demonstrates%20a%20%26quot%3Bhuge%20gap%26quot%3B%20in%20political%20advertising%20rules.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Federal%20Elections%20Commission%20requires%20clear%20ad%20disclaimers%20on%20broadcast%2C%20newspaper%2C%20and%20internet%20content%20detailing%20who%20paid%20for%20the%20ad.%20But%20the%20rules%20don't%20extend%20to%20paid%20influencers.%20In%20January%2C%20the%20Brennan%20Center%20sent%20a%20legal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.brennancenter.org%2Four-work%2Fresearch-reports%2Fcomment-fec-adopt-updated-rules-requiring-transparency-paid-influencers%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eletter%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20FEC%20asking%20it%20to%20add%20disclosure%20requirements%20for%20when%20candidates%20pay%20influencers%20for%20their%20online%20support.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20illustrates%20the%20potency%20of%20influencers%20and%20other%20more%20novel%20methods%20of%20political%20communication%20as%20tools%20for%20foreign%20interference%20in%20the%20electoral%20process%2C%26quot%3B%20Weiner%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20two%20plaintiffs%2C%20both%20employees%20at%20RT%2C%20a%20Russian%20media%20organization%2C%20attempted%20to%20%26quot%3Binfluence%20the%20American%20public%20by%20secretly%20planting%20and%20financing%20a%20content%20creation%20company%20on%20US%20soil%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20posted%20videos%20on%20X%2C%20TikTok%2C%20Instagram%2C%20and%20YouTube%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Justice%20Department.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20in%20question%20is%20Tenet%20Media.%20The%20Justice%20Department%20didn't%20name%20the%20company%20in%20its%20filing%2C%20but%20there%20were%20enough%20details%20for%20anyone%20paying%20attention%20to%20figure%20it%20out.%20The%20Tennessee-based%20group%20publishes%20content%20from%20podcasters%20and%20influencers%20like%20Tim%20Pool%20and%20Benny%20Johnson%2C%20who%20said%20they%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpro-trump-influencers-say-had-no-idea-russia-funding-videos-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edid%20not%20know%20about%20Tenet's%20ties%20to%20Russian%3C%2Fa%3E%20funding.%20Garland%20confirmed%20in%20a%20press%20conference%20that%20Tenet%20did%20not%20disclose%20those%20ties%20to%20its%20influencers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20there%20are%20disclosure%20requirements%20for%20online%20political%20ads%2C%20they%20mostly%20apply%20%26quot%3Bto%20those%20traditional%20pop-up%20ads%20that%20you%20would%20see%20that%20were%20prevalent%2010%20years%20ago%20or%20so%2C%26quot%3B%20Weiner%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20influencers%20and%20for%20other%20really%20novel%20forms%20of%20communication%2C%20there's%20really%20almost%20no%20transparency%2C%20and%20that's%20a%20problem.%20There's%20no%20real%20transparency%20via%20regulation%2C%20and%20there's%20limited-to-no%20transparency%20even%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20voluntary%20rules%20that%20major%20online%20platforms%20have%20adopted%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESocial%20media%20platforms%20have%20adopted%20advertising%20libraries%20to%20increase%20ad%20transparency.%20Meta%2C%20for%20example%2C%20adopted%20an%20ad%20library%20that%20%26quot%3Bincludes%20all%20active%20and%20public%20branded%20content%20that's%20shown%20on%20Facebook%20and%20Instagram%20with%20a%20paid%20partnership%20label%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20its%20website.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20such%20databases%2C%20Weiner%20said%2C%20generally%20apply%20only%20to%20traditional%20requests%20to%20purchase%20advertising.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%2C%20instead%2C%20you%20pay%20an%20influencer%20who's%20active%20on%20a%20site%2C%20there's%20no%20way%20necessarily%20for%20the%20platform%20to%20know%20that%20that%20person%20was%20being%20paid%2C%26quot%3B%20Weiner%20said%2C%20noting%20the%20Federal%20Trade%20Commission%20requires%20influencers%20to%20disclose%20if%20brands%20are%20paying%20them%20to%20promote%20products.%20%26quot%3BBut%2C%20generally%2C%20even%20there%2C%20that%20mostly%20applies%20to%20commercial%20transactions.%20There's%20really%20nothing%20when%20you're%20talking%20about%20influencers%20paid%20for%20political%20purposes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foutdated-us-election-law-loophole-allows-russia-pay-influencers-tenet-2024-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1725831739000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66de08e5a0ff598b2665a6c4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foutdated-us-election-law-loophole-allows-russia-pay-influencers-tenet-2024-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Russia%2C%20which%20has%20long%20worked%20to%20sway%20American%20elections%2C%20has%20found%20a%20new%20and%20legal%20way%20in.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kbalevic%40businessinsider.com%20(Katie%20Balevic)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A57%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foutdated-us-election-law-loophole-allows-russia-pay-influencers-tenet-2024-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%225%20of%2