content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221920%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Old%20people%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6673f9c6a76074d191cd486f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EEconomists%20are%20warning%20that%20Europe's%20aging%20population%20could%20drive%20a%20slowdown%20in%20growth%20on%20the%20continent.%3Cp%3EJanina%20Steinmetz%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20global%20population%20is%20getting%20older.%20%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20trend%20will%20lead%20to%20lower%20returns%2C%20earnings%20growth%2C%20and%20valuations%2C%20JPMorgan%20strategists%20say.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIf%20the%20share%20of%20people%20over%2065%20increases%201%25%2C%20returns%20will%20decline%200.92%25%2C%20they%20estimate.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20aging%20of%20the%20world%20population%20is%20expected%20to%20accelerate%20in%20the%20coming%20decades%2C%20which%20will%20likely%20produce%20bad%20outcomes%20for%20the%20stock%20market%2C%20JPMorgan%20strategists%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20strategists%20say%20that%20historically%2C%20an%20older%20population%20has%20led%20to%20declining%20returns%2C%20lower%20earnings%20growth%2C%20and%20weaker%20valuations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20a%2010-year%20period%2C%20a%201%25%20increase%20in%20the%20number%20of%20people%20over%2065%20is%20correlated%20with%20a%200.92%25%20decline%20in%20annual%20stock%20returns%2C%20the%20strategists%20calculated%20in%20a%20report%20released%20last%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20point%20mainly%20to%20slower%20growth%20and%20falling%20valuations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20an%20older%20investor%20base%20looking%20to%20save%20for%20retirement%2C%20investment%20capital%20declines%2C%20leading%20to%20less%20innovation.%20That%2C%20plus%20slower%20growth%20in%20the%20workforce%2C%20will%20have%20a%20negative%20impact%20on%20earnings%20growth%2C%20the%20strategists%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDomestic%20population%20aging%20may%20reduce%20earnings%20growth%20for%20several%20reasons.%20It%20leads%20to%20slower%20workforce%20growth%2C%20reducing%20domestic%20economic%20growth.%20There%20is%20also%20evidence%20that%20aging%20can%20reduce%20innovation%20and%20productivity%20growth%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20strategists%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20especially%20true%20for%20companies%20that%20derive%20revenue%20from%20international%20operations%2C%20the%20strategists%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20companies%20that%20derive%20more%20of%20their%20revenue%20from%20abroad%2C%20like%20multinationals%2C%20global%20population%20aging%20(in%20a%20GDP-weighted%20sense)%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20more%20consequential%20for%20earnings%20growth%20than%20local%20population%20aging%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20strategists%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20means%20equity%20market%20indexes%20with%20small%20and%20mid-caps%20will%20likely%20see%20more%20impact%20from%20local%20population%20aging%20than%20those%20with%20exclusively%20large%20caps.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EValuations%20will%20also%20take%20a%20hit%2C%20the%20strategists%20said.%20As%20the%20elderly%20empty%20their%20retirement%20funds%2C%20national%20savings%20decline%2C%20thus%20raising%20bond%20yields.%20Older%20populations%20also%20pull%20out%20of%20the%20market%20at%20higher%20rates%2C%20driving%20down%20stock%20prices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20trends%2C%20plus%20lower%20earnings%20growth%20expectations%2C%20justify%20lower%20valuations%2C%20the%20strategists%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20strategists%20say%20there's%20one%20bright%20spot%2C%20though.%20That's%20healthcare%2C%20which%20older%20populations%20tend%20to%20spend%20more%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20find%20a%20clear%20positive%20relationship%20between%20aging%20and%20excess%20returns%20on%20the%20sector%2C%20driven%20entirely%20by%20faster%20earnings%20growth%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20strategists%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%201%25%20increase%20in%20the%20population%20share%20of%20those%20over%2065%20will%20lead%20to%20a%200.85%25%20increase%20in%20health%20care%20returns%20over%20a%2010-year%20period%2C%20the%20strategists%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20strategists%20note%2C%20too%2C%20that%20the%20populating%20aging%20trend%20won't%20impact%20countries%20equally.%20In%20China%2C%20the%20elderly%20share%20of%20the%20population%20is%20set%20to%20increase%20by%20seven%20percentage%20points%20in%20the%20next%20decade.%20The%20US%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20will%20see%20a%20more%20moderate%20rise%20from%2018.1%25%20to%2021.5%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPast%20reports%20have%20also%20warned%20of%20the%20aging%20population's%20impact%20on%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20year%2C%20Barclays%20economist%20Jonathan%20Millar%20said%20boomers%2C%20a%20historically%20large%20generation%2C%20are%20approaching%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbaby-boomer-gen-z-millennials-economy-housing-job-market-stocks-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bpeak%20burden%26quot%3B%20on%20the%20US%20economy%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20next%20few%20years.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Frecession-economy-outlook-us-stock-market-ownership-old-americans-retirement-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20larger%20share%20of%20people%20over%2055%25%20owning%20stocks%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20US%20may%20be%20a%20downside%20risk%20to%20the%20market%2C%20as%20older%20investors%20often%20don't%20have%20the%20luxury%20of%20holding%20through%20a%20downturn%20and%20could%20exacerbate%20volatility%20by%20selling%20during%20market%20pullbacks.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faging-world-population-stock-market-risk-jpmorgan-returns-valuations-growth-2024-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1725798662000%2C%22visual%22%