20just%20about%20everything%20are%20in%20a%20tough%20spot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%20are%20now%20grappling%20with%20the%20emergence%20of%20a%20more%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fconsumer-spending-decline-how-retailers-respond-inflation-prices-walmart-costco-2024-6%23%3A~%3Atext%3DUS%2520consumer%2520spending%2520%25E2%2580%2594%2520especially%2520on%2C%252C%2520restaurants%252C%2520and%2520other%2520experiences.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprice-conscious%20consumer%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20they%20have%20seen%20in%20years.%20Many%20people%20have%20drawn%20down%20their%20excess%20savings%20from%20the%20pandemic%20and%20are%20becoming%20painfully%20aware%20of%20the%20accumulated%20price%20increases%2C%20even%20as%20inflation%20has%20come%20down%20from%20multi-decade%20highs%20seen%20in%20the%20middle%20of%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20survey%20conducted%20by%20McKinsey%20%26amp%3B%20Company%2C%2076%25%20of%20US%20consumers%20said%20they%20expected%20to%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mckinsey.com%2Findustries%2Fconsumer-packaged-goods%2Four-insights%2Fthe-state-of-the-us-consumer%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etrade%20down%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20over%20the%20third%20quarter%2C%20which%20includes%20things%20like%20delaying%20purchases%2C%20searching%20for%20discounts%2C%20or%20opting%20for%20a%20buy%20now%2C%20pay%20later%20plan%20at%20checkout.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20that%20Americans%20have%20stopped%20spending.%20US%20retail%20sales%20came%20in%20stronger%20than%20expected%20in%20July%2C%20with%20Americans%20spending%20more%20overall%20compared%20to%20the%20prior%20month%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.census.gov%2Fretail%2Fsales.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECensus%3C%2Fa%3E%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20consumers%20are%20flashing%20signs%20that%20they're%20way%20more%20eager%20to%20bargain%20hunt%2C%20and%20more%20picky%20on%20what%20they%20splurge%20on%2C%20according%20to%20Ted%20Rossman%2C%20a%20senior%20industry%20analyst%20at%20Bankrate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmericans%20are%20still%20willing%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-consumer-spending-international-travel-entertainment-surge-savings-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshell%20out%20for%20experiences%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Rossman%20said%2C%20pointing%20to%20success%20among%20airlines%20and%20travel-oriented%20firms.%20However%2C%20they%20seem%20to%20have%20tired%20out%20on%20goods.%20Around%2040%25%20of%20consumers%20said%20they%20planned%20to%20pare%20back%20spending%20on%20accessories%2C%20home%20decor%2C%20jewelry%2C%20and%20furniture%2C%20per%20McKinsey's%20survey.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20like%2C%20people%20are%20going%20to%20spend%2C%20but%20they're%20only%20going%20to%20spend%20when%20they%20feel%20like%20there's%20really%20value%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20Rossman%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECustomers%20have%20likely%20refined%20their%20spending%20habits%2C%20with%20more%20Americans%20now%20searching%20for%20high-quality%20products%20at%20a%20good%20value%2C%20according%20to%20Simeon%20Siegel%2C%20a%20senior%20retail%20and%20ecommerce%20analyst%20at%20BMO.%20That's%20why%20firms%20at%20the%20low-end%20%E2%80%94%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmcdonalds-expensive-prices-too-high-fast-food-restaurant-falling-sales-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMcDonald's%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20as%20well%20as%20on%20the%20high-end%20%E2%80%94%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstarbucks-lvmh-loreal-declining-sales-china-earnings-consumer-luxury-retail-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELVMH%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20are%20struggling%2C%20he%20said.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20many%20retailers%20that%20saw%20an%20across-the-board%20boom%20in%20profits%20amid%20post-pandemic%20revenge%20shopping%2C%20it's%20the%20e